SpriteJS Project Overview:

Spritejs is a cross platform high-performance graphics system, which can render graphics on web, node, desktop applications and mini-programs. SpriteJS Next is the new version of spritejs. It is renderer agnostic enabling the same api to render in multiple contexts: webgl

the same api to render in multiple contexts: webgl2, webgl, and canvas2d.

Key Features:
- Manipulate the sprites element as you do with the DOM elements
- Rendering by WebGL2 context
- Multiple layers support
- DOM Events handling
- Object Oriented Programming with ES6+
- OffscreenCanvas and Web Wo

Programming with ES6+
- OffscreenCanvas and Web Worker support
- Integration with d3.js
- Server-side rendering capabilities
- Vue.js integration

Usage:
- Browser: <script src="https://unpkg.com/spritejs@3/dist/spritejs.min.js"></script>
- Node.js: npm install spritejs --save
- 3D Extension: sprite

npm install spritejs --save
- 3D Extension: sprite-extend-3d library for 3D rendering

Core Classes: Scene, Sprite, Layer
Rendering Contexts: WebGL2, WebGL, Canvas2D

SpriteJS Class Hierarchy and Architecture:

Base Classes:
- Node: Root base class for all sprite elements
- Block: Base class for block-level elements (extends Node)
- Path: Base class for path-based shapes (extends Node)
- Group: Container class for grouping elements (extends Block)

Shape Classes

- Ring: Ring/Donut shape (extends Path)
- Polyline: Multi-point line (extends Path)
